1Ô∏è‚É£. What is JavaScript?
JavaScript (JS) is a high-level, interpreted programming language primarily used to make web pages interactive. It is one of the core technologies of the web, alongside HTML and CSS.

2Ô∏è‚É£. Why Learn JavaScript?
Interactivity: Adds dynamic behavior to websites (animations, pop-ups, form validation).
Versatility: Used for both frontend (websites) and backend (servers with Node.js).
Popularity: One of the most widely used programming languages.
Job Opportunities: Many careers require JavaScript skills.

